  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Quadratic equation from school fundraising ticket sales</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>
During a school fundraising event, tickets were sold in two groups. The first group sold \(x\) tickets, while the second group sold \(x + {@k@}\) tickets. Altogether, {@T@} tickets were sold.
</p>

<p>
(a) Form a quadratic equation representing this situation.
</p>

<p>
<strong>Equation</strong> [[input:eqn1]] [[validation:eqn1]] [[feedback:prt1]]
</p>

<p>
(b) Determine the value of \(x\).
</p>

<p>
\(x =\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt2]]
</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
Let the number of tickets sold by the first group be \(x\).
</p>

<p>
The second group sold \(x + {@k@}\) tickets.
</p>

<p>
The total number of tickets sold was {@T@}.
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Form the equation.
</p>

<p>
\[
x(x + {@k@}) = {@T@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Expand the expression.
</p>

<p>
\[
x^2 + {@k@}x = {@T@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Rearrange the equation into standard quadratic form.
</p>

<p>
\[
x^2 + {@k@}x - {@T@} = 0
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 4: Factorise the quadratic expression.
</p>

<p>
\[
(x - {@n@})(x + {@n + k@}) = 0
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 5: Solve each factor.
</p>

<p>
First factor:
</p>

<p>
\[
x - {@n@} = 0
\]
</p>

<p>
Add {@n@} to both sides:
</p>

<p>
\[
x = {@n@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Second factor:
</p>

<p>
\[
x + {@n + k@} = 0
\]
</p>

<p>
Subtract {@n + k@} from both sides:
</p>

<p>
\[
x = -{@n + k@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Since the number of tickets sold cannot be negative, we reject the negative solution.
</p>

<p>
Therefore,
</p>

<p>
\[
x = {@n@}
\]
</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
